    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Fredericksburg Savings Institution conducted business during the mid-nineteenth century in Fredericksburg, Virginia.
</p>
      <p>The minute book was used as an exhibit in an unidentified suit.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Fredericksburg Savings Institution Minute Book, 1839-1844, records meetings of the company's stockholders. Information found in the minutes includes date and location of meetings; names of stockholders; election of officers; reports made by treasurer and clerk; resolutions; and decisions made by stockholders related to the activities of the bank. 
</p>
    </scopecontent>
